AGI - The Assembly of the Cdr and the trustees of the Rai> has proclaimed to a wide majority (8 votes against and a prisoner) the state of agitation > and has entrusted Usigrai a package of 5 days strike >. The Assembly, reads in a note, "confirms the will to transform the Public Service in the megaphone of the parties >, and to the company the shortcomings of heads dropped from above that would empty Radio1 of its vocation to the news", as well as "the lack of will to indirect a public selection to replace the more than 100 colleagues out of the Raiup in recent years, the lack of respect for the trade union agreements on the organics in the Tgr, the result
&nbsp;
In the document approved by the Assembly of the Boards and the trustees of the Rai, convened online by Usigrai, it is expressed "very concern for the stalemate situation in which the company pays: While on the one hand there is the escape of some of the faces known of the Rai towards other competitors, > with inevitable repercussions also on the corporate audits and budgets, on the other, the autonomy of the Public Service from the policy">.&nbsp;The Assembly of the Boards is still read in the document, "Concord with the Usigrai: Public Service cannot be the megaphone of parties. A position of the union that has had an echo outside the national borders: An international mission on freedom of press in our country is indispensable. Not only that, the information is the great absent in the Industrial Plan. There are no guidelines on the impact that the transformation into digital media company will have on the journalistic sector.
&nbsp;
In the working groups 'Optimization editorial offer' and 'Evoluzione competences and organizational interventions' there are no journalists, and for now the only interventions, dropped from above without any comparison with the union, are those that preview the dismemberment of the Radio, with Gr Parliament and the sports editorial staff that would be assigned respectively to Rai Parliament and Rai Sport, emptying in fact Radio1 from its vocation to news based on information and no industrial advantage, without any reasonable motivation.
&nbsp;
All this, we still read in the document, "in a framework of lack of respect for the trade union agreements on the organics of the regional newspaper head and of lack of turn over in the national newspapers, which in fact produce a reduction of the occupational perimeter. Over 100 non-replaced outputs in recent years, resulting in higher workloads in the face of an increase in information products. All this with continuous budget cuts for the troupes and lack of resources to proceed to the stabilization of precarious colleagues working in the programs, as the Rai has committed to doing with the so-called phase 2". &nbsp;In addition, notes the Assembly of the Boards and Trustees, "the fact that the Rai has repeatedly reiterated that it does not want to proceed to a public selection, the only one that allows transparent access in the company, prevents the colleagues and colleagues of the Tgr from being able to transfer to reunite with family members or for legitimate professional ambitions.
&nbsp;
At the same time, transfers of colleagues and colleagues from genres to nationals, > in the absence of competitive rankings, facilitate the so-called 'pre-uses' by direct call in programs, while the Rai Code of Ethics imposes 'the use of contextual procedures or in any case to objective criteria of selection' and in fact create new precarious". And again: "For years, the company has not replaced maternity allowances, obtaining indirectly an economic advantage and increasing, even in this case, the workload of the drafts", is underlined in the approved document, and "last, in this worrying framework, the cancellation of the agreement on the result award, with the motivation of wanting to align it with that of other professional categories.
&nbsp;
The assembly finds unacceptable what the company expects to the union, that it does not want to foresee, that is, a fixed part as for the other employees and to want to tie the dispensing to the general listening results of the Rai and not to those of the major editions of the news, as from previous agreement. In fact, by making journalists pay with a cut the waste and any wrong editorial choices of the top, which are not called instead to respond". For all these reasons, the Assembly of Cdr and Rai's trustees proclaimed the "state of agitation that marks the start of a mobilization" and entrusted to the Usigrai a package "up to 5 days of strike". &nbsp;

