AGI - Fifty million euros to directly support the budget of the Tunisian State, focusing on energy efficiency and renewable energies, but also a credit line for small and medium-sized Tunisian enterprises, worth 55 million euros, and a protocol of understanding between the Ministry of the University and Italian Research and the homologue dicastery Tunisia. The fourth mission in Tunis of Giorgia Meloni as President of the Council is realized with these "three very important agreements", as Meloni himself defined in a statement at the end of the visit to the Palace of Carthage.
The premier was a few hours in the Tunisian capital, where she arrived this morning. I would like to say that we have to take a look at the situation in the Community. Accompanied by the Interior Ministers and the University and Research, respectively Matteo Piantedosi and Anna Maria Bernini, and the Deputy Foreign Minister Edmondo Cirielli, Meloni first had a conversation with Saied, then the three agreements were signed, which fall into the Mattei Plan.
"The collaboration with Tunisia, also thanks to the Italian commitment, has become a priority for the EU," said the President of the Council, and "I am very proud of the work that Italy has carried out and that has contributed to the signature of the memorandum" of understanding between Tunisia and the EU, which "has laid the foundations for an equal model with the countries of the enlarged Mediterranean". "In the coming weeks - Meloni announced - many other agreements will be signed. The Minister of Defense Guido Crosetto, Minister of Culture Gennaro Sangiuliano, Minister of Education Giuseppe Valditara will be present here in Tunisia.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
There is therefore a constant presence of the Italian government and this cooperation brings many results". Among these, he said, "I think about the management of migration, on which I want once again to thank the Tunisian authorities, President Saied, for a work we try to carry out together against the traffickers of being human. Clearly we know that Tunisia cannot become the country of arrival of migrants. On this we must strengthen cooperation, we want to involve international organizations and work on repatriations, but we want to work mainly on regular flows".
The goal, Meloni stressed, "is to fight the slavers of the third millennium, the Mafia organizations who think they exploit the legitimate aspirations of people. It's a job we share with President Saied." That with Tunisia, Meloni concluded, "is a very important strategic relationship with a work that we carry forward together with 360 degrees". "The Mattei Plan - it has observed the Bernini ministra - is a strategic initiative of the government in which also high formation represents a pillar. We have the ambitious goal of providing young Africans with the tools to actively participate in the progress and growth of their countries. It is our duty to support scientific research and cooperation with partner countries, such as Tunisia, to win the global challenges we are facing, starting from the contrast to climate change, agricultural innovation and biodiversity protection." Bernini signed a Memorandum of Understanding (Mou) with the Tunisian counterpart, Moncef Boukthir, to strengthen the scientific partnership with the aim of developing joint research projects in areas considered strategic. &nbsp;

